The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Shrachi mulls public issue

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Ravi Todi in Calcutta on Thursday. A Telegraph picture

 Calcutta, June 16: Shrachi Securities (P) Ltd is planning to tap the capital market to fund its expansion plan.

 Managing director Ravi Todi said the public issue would be launched this fiscal. We will file with the Sebi soon.

 The promoters hold 52.07 per cent in the company, which is listed at Calcutta and Bombay Stock Exchanges. Todi said the scrip would be listed on the NSE also. The companys stock closed at Rs 34.10 on the BSE today.

 The last issue of Shrachi took place in 1994.

 The board has decided to increase the authorised share capital from Rs 10 crore to Rs 20 crore. 

 The company had changed its name to Shrachi Infrastructure Finance Ltd to reflect its true identity.

 Our main business is financing critical infrastructure inputs like commercial vehicles. We are also stepping up the financing of infrastructure equipment, he said, while announcing the companys results here.

 Last year, Shrachis profit before tax and extraordinary items rose 98.68 per cent at Rs 7.21 crore, while profit after tax grew 79 per cent to Rs 5.4 crore.

 The disbursement for commercial vehicles grew by over 80 per cent. It is expecting a total disbursement of Rs 1,000 crore for 2005-06.

 Todi said he is expecting a 30 per cent growth, although spreads are under pressure. 




